      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "test(qa): route DM baseline through channel scenario driver",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nThe QA real-E2E migration plan needs channel scenarios to be routed through a reusable behavior contract instead of hand-wiring low-level `state.addInboundMessage` / `waitForOutboundMessage` calls in every YAML file. Without that shared path, live, Crabline, and qa-channel variants can drift and weak scenarios can look covered while skipping thread/reply/no-reply semantics.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdds the QA Lab channel behavior scenario module with typed scenario definitions, expected reply/no-reply steps, restart/thread/reply requirement summaries, target/message helpers, and a `ChannelScenarioDriver` interface.\n\nThis also wires one concrete existing scenario through that path: `qa/scenarios/channels/dm-chat-baseline.yaml` now uses a native `conversation:` flow action, so the YAML defines target, sender, turns, and expectations while the runtime API owns the QA-channel driver plumbing.\n\nThe runner deliberately fails fast for reply-targeting steps until those semantics are implemented, and created-thread reply expectations are pinned to the dynamic thread id to avoid false-positive threaded evidence.\n\nAI-assisted: yes.\n\n## User Impact\n\nNo end-user runtime behavior change. QA authors now have a shared contract and a working concise example for routing channel behavior through a pluggable driver, with `dm-chat-baseline` proving the path against the existing qa-channel suite.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/qa-lab/src/channel-behavior-scenario.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/scenario-flow-runner.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/scenario-runtime-api.test.ts --reporter=verbose` pass, 23 tests.\n- `pnpm openclaw qa suite --provider-mode mock-openai --scenario dm-chat-baseline --output-dir .artifacts/qa-e2e/dm-channel-runtime-helper-smoke` pass, 1 scenario passed / 0 failed.\n- `pnpm openclaw qa suite --provider-mode mock-openai --scenario dm-chat-baseline --output-dir .artifacts/qa-e2e/dm-channel-native-yaml-smoke` pass after converting the scenario definition to native YAML.\n- `pnpm openclaw qa suite --provider-mode mock-openai --scenario dm-chat-baseline --output-dir .artifacts/qa-e2e/dm-channel-conversation-action-cyclefix-smoke` pass after adding the native `conversation` flow action and cycle fix.\n- `pnpm check:architecture` pass after moving QA transport bus types to the leaf protocol module.\n- `pnpm check:test-types` pass.\n- `pnpm deadcode:unused-files` pass.\n- `pnpm deadcode:dependencies` pass.\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check extensions/qa-lab/src/channel-behavior-scenario.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/channel-behavior-scenario.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/scenario-runtime-api.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/scenario-runtime-api.test.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/runtime-api.ts extensions/qa-lab/src/scenario-flow-runner.test.ts qa/scenarios/channels/dm-chat-baseline.yaml` pass.\n- `git diff --check` pass.\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` clean after simplification.\n\n\n",
        "branch": "dallin/qa-channel-scenario-driver",
